<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-24T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-24T15:00:00-05:00" n="878" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d878">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">681.003/198a: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-24T16:00:00-04:00">July
                                        24, 1935—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>48. Since matter of recognition of Spanish Zone by this Government
                                and the settlement of claims by Spain has been pending for
                                approximately 6 months, the Foreign Office having informed the
                                Embassy in February it was pressing for an answer from the Spanish
                                High Commissioner at Tetuan, you are requested, within your
                                discretion, to ascertain orally, if possible, what the Spanish
                                Government proposes to do in the matter. It would appear that
                                sufficient time has elapsed for a decision upon the question. Please
                                cable brief reply.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>